videos.description: On his 21st birthday, D.J. Reed takes the ball away from West Virginia receiver David Sills V for the first takeaway of the game.
videos.headline: Kansas State's Reed forces turnover to start his birthday

videos.description: D.J. Reed intercepts West Virginia quarterback Will Grier for his second takeaway of the game.
videos.headline: Reed continues birthday celebration with INT

videos.description: Will Grier hits Ka'Raun White in stride who takes it 75-yards to the house for the first West Virginia touchdown of the game.
videos.headline: Grier hits White for 75-yard WVU TD

videos.description: David Sills V grabs his 17th touchdown reception of the season on a 16-yard touchdown pass from Will Grier.
videos.headline: West Virginia's Sills grabs 16-yard TD

videos.description: Kansas State fullback Winston Dimel punches in a touchdown from short distance.
videos.headline: Kansas State's Dimel pounds in 1-yard TD

videos.description: Denzel Goolsby grabs the tipped ball to intercept West Virginia's Will Grier.
videos.headline: Kansas State's Goolsby picks off Grier

videos.description: Will Grier escapes a sack, scrambles and hits Gary Jennings for a 43-yard completion.
videos.headline: West Virginia's Grier avoids sack, throws 43-yard pass to Jennings

videos.description: West Virginia's David Sills V makes diving touchdown catch while dragging his toe in bounds.
videos.headline: Sills makes unbelievable TD catch

videos.description: Kansas State fullback Winston Dimel takes another goal line carry into the end zone for a touchdown.
videos.headline: Dimel punches in his 2nd TD

videos.description: Ezekial Rose intercepts Skylar Thompson's attempted screen pass with 10 seconds left in the first half.
videos.headline: West Virginia's Rose intercepts Thompson

videos.description: Will Grier scrambles and chucks it in the end zone where Ka'Raun White catches it as time expires in the first half.
videos.headline: West Virginia completes hail mary TD to end half

videos.description: West Virginia head coach Dana Holgorsen says they need protect the ball in the second half to maintain the lead.
videos.headline: Holgorsen happy to have first half lead despite turnovers

videos.description: Fullback Winston Dimel comes up with a 33-yard reception after the ball is tipped in the air by a West Virginia defensive back.
videos.headline: Kansas State's Dimel catches ball off tip drill

videos.description: Kenny Robinson picks off Kansas State quarterback Skylar Thompson in the red zone.
videos.headline: West Virginia's Robinson gets clutch INT to stop driving Kansas State

videos.description: West Virginia head coach Dana Holgorsen credits the play of his defense in their 28-23 win over Kansas State.
videos.headline: Holgorsen says defense 'bailed us out'

videos.description: West Virginia quarterback Will Grier says he is happy they came out with a win despite having multiple turnovers.
videos.headline: Grier likes the way the team played together
